addPool(uint40,uint16).details: User receives the reward for the normal shares, and the reward for the locked shares additional to that. This is why 10_00 will total to a x1.1 multiplier.

params.multiplier_: Multiplier that applies to the pool. 10_00 is multiplier of x1.1, 100_00 is x2.0.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

availableLiquidity().details: The available liquidity is reduced by the minimum amount to make sure no rounding errors occur when liquidity is drained.

returns._0: The total available liquidity in the pool.
bool true if the user is able to transfer their shares
bool true if the user is able to withdraw their shares

params.easyXOwner_: The address of the easyX owner.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

params.assets_: The amount of the collateral asset to deposit.
params.minShares_: The desired minimum amount to receive in exchange for the deposited collateral. Reverts otherwise.

returns._0: The amount of shares received for the deposited collateral.

params.assets_: The amount of the collateral asset to deposit.
params.minShares_: The desired minimum amount to receive in exchange for the deposited collateral. Reverts otherwise.
params.poolId_: Id of the pool to lock the deposit

returns._0: The amount of shares received for the deposited collateral.

params.amount_: the amount of fees to deposit

depositProfit(uint256).details: the allowande of the sender needs to be sufficient

params.profit_: the profit of the asset with respect to the asset multiplier

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params.defaultLockTime_: The default lock time of the pool.
params.earlyWithdrawalFee_: The early withdrawal fee of the pool.
params.earlyWithdrawalTime_: The early withdrawal time of the pool.
params.minimumAmount_: The minimum amount of the pool (subtracted from available liquidity).
params.name_: The name of the pool's ERC20 liquidity token.
params.symbol_: The symbol of the pool's ERC20 liquidity token.

params.poolId_: Id of the pool to lock the deposit
params.shares_: The amount of shares to lock.

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

params.poolId_: the id of the pool to preview
params.user_: the user to get the pool details for

returns.userPool: the UserPoolDetails. This informs about current user's locked and unlocked shares

returns.userPools: an array of UserPoolDetails. This informs about current user's locked and unlocked shares

params.poolId_: the id of the pool to convert
params.poolShares_: the amount of pool shares to convert

returns._0: the amount of assets that would be received

requestLossPayout(uint256).details: pays out the loss when msg.sender is a registered liquidity pool adapter

params.loss_: the requested amount of the asset with respect to the asset multiplier

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

params.poolId_: the id of the pool to unlock the shares from
params.poolShares_: the amount of pool shares to unlock

params.multiplier_: Multiplier that applies to the pool. 10_00 is multiplier of x1.1, 100_00 is x2.0.
params.poolId_: Id of the pool to update

params.minOut_: The desired minimum amount of collateral to receive in exchange for the withdrawn shares. Reverts otherwise.
params.shares_: The amount of shares to withdraw.

returns._0: The amount of collateral received for the withdrawn shares.

addPool(uint40,uint16).notice: Add pool with a lock time and a multiplier

availableLiquidity().notice: Returns the total available liquidity in the pool.

canTransferLps(address).notice: Function to check if a user is able to transfer their shares to another address

canWithdrawLps(address).notice: Function to check if a user is able to withdraw their shares, with a possible loss to earlyWithdrawalFee

deposit(uint256,uint256).notice: Deposits an amount of the collateral asset.

depositAndLock(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Deposits an amount of the collateral asset and locks it directly

depositFees(uint256).notice: Deposits fees from the protocol into this liquidity pool. Distributes assets over the liquidity providers by increasing LP shares.

depositProfit(uint256).notice: deposits a protocol profit when a trader made a loss

earlyWithdrawalFee().notice: Relative fee to early withdraw non-locked shares.

earlyWithdrawalTime().notice: Time when the early withdrawal fee is applied shares.

easyXOwner().notice: Contract that holds the address of EasyX owner

lastDepositTime(address).notice: Last deposit time of a user.

minimumAmount().notice: minimum amount of asset to stay in the pool.

pools(uint256).notice: Array of pools with different lock time and multipliers.

previewPoolOf(address,uint256).notice: Returns information about user's pool deposits. Including locked and unlocked pool shares, shares and assets.

previewPoolsOf(address).notice: Returns information about user's pool deposits. Including locked and unlocked pool shares, shares and assets.

previewRedeemPoolShares(uint256,uint256).notice: Preview function to convert locked pool shares to asset

requestLossPayout(uint256).notice: requests payout of a protocol loss when a trader made a profit

unlockShares(uint256,uint256).notice: Unlocks shares and returns them to the user.

userPoolInfo(uint256,address).notice: Mapping of UserPoolInfo for each user for each pool. userPoolInfo[poolId][user]

userWithdrawalFee(address).notice: Returns a possible earlyWithdrawalFee for a user. Fee applies when the user withdraws after the earlyWithdrawalTime and before the defaultLockTime

withdraw(uint256,uint256).notice: Withdraws an amount of the collateral asset.

withdrawFromPool(uint256,uint256,uint256.notice: Unlocks and withdraws an amount of the collateral asset.
